Refactor this code to be explicit and maintainable.

Constraints:

- Prioritize readability over brevity.
- Do not use clever or condensed logic.
- Do not introduce abstractions unless they remove obvious duplication and improve clarity.
- Prefer explicit conditionals over nested expressions.
- Prefer named intermediate variables over inline compound expressions.
- Keep control flow boring and obvious.
- Use descriptive function and variable names.
- Keep functions small, but do not split code into tiny helpers unless it improves readability.
- Match the existing project style.

Done when:

- A mid-level engineer can understand the code quickly.
- The main path is easy to trace line by line.
- There are no surprising shortcuts or “smart” tricks.
- Behavior stays the same.
